http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/%E2%80%98Situation-no-different-in-Delhi%E2%80%99/article14003811.ece

Annapurna Singh first touched a bike when she was in Class X. Now 30, her love for them has only grown since. Not surprisingly, the journey has not been easy.“I am from Dhanbad in Jharkhand. In small towns, a woman riding a bike is nothing less than a taboo. Men would taunt on the streets. Surprisingly, the situation is no different in Delhi. People can accept a girl riding a scooty, but not a bike. The Bikerni has given me a new identity,” she said.Having saved for over a year, the HR manager finally bought a Splendor Plus a while ago.